OL,3,CBiker's plea: Please look out for us
OL,5,FShe said: "The bike went over the
OL,6,Fcentral reservation and landed in the
OL,7,Fmiddle of the opposite lane.
OL,8,FThankfully the traffic lights on the
OL,9,Fother side must have been on red,
OL,10,Fbecause there was no immediate
OL,11,Ftraffic. If there had, it would have
OL,12,Fbeen carnage.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
