OL,3,CBiker's plea: Please look out for us
OL,5,FShe said: "When the police came to
OL,6,Ftake an interview the next week, they
OL,7,Fsaid 'we didn't think you were going
OL,8,Fto make it'. They were convinced
OL,9,Fneither one of us had any severe
OL,10,Ftraumas purely by chance. The bike was
OL,11,Fa write-off completely.
OL,13,F"The driver's comment was 'they came
OL,14,Ffrom nowhere'. We didn't - we came
OL,15,Falong the same road as everybody else.
OL,16,FWe were going the same speed as
OL,17,Feverybody else. The bike was red and
OL,18,Fit had lights on it, it was broad
OL,19,Fdaylight, it was good conditions with
OL,20,Fno rain. It was late afternoon, and
OL,21,Fthe traffic was light."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
